{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"4277d85693ce7ae3559eb0a94f3b50be93446600"},"timestamp":1324308607,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjAxMzY0","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/232","origin":"github"},"title":"config/auto/sizes/test_c.in uses wrong format specifier to print sizes","message":"_config/auto/sizes/test_c.in_ uses the specifier `%u` to print values of type `size_t`, which is not portable and in particular should fail on 64-bit big-endian architectures.\n\nAs the correct specifier `%zu` is a C99 addition, it's probably best to convert the value to `unsigned`:\n\n```\ndiff --git a/config/auto/sizes/test_c.in b/config/auto/sizes/test_c.in\nindex a6bd08a..7236d24 100644\n--- a/config/auto/sizes/test_c.in\n+++ b/config/auto/sizes/test_c.in\n@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@ figure out some Configure settings\n int\n main(int argc, char **argv)\n {\n-    printf(\"%u\\n\", sizeof (@TEMP_type@));\n+    printf(\"%u\\n\", (unsigned)sizeof (@TEMP_type@));\n     return EXIT_SUCCESS;\n }\n```","files":null}]}